headline: 3 Reasons to Sell REGN and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, Regeneron’s stock price fell to $587.01. Shareholders have lost 11.7% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 17.5%. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
